Birds of Illinois Key to Terms regular: Species for which there are recorded sightings in at least eight of the past 10 years.
casual: Species for which there are accepted sighting records in three to seven of the past 10 years.
accidental: Species for which there are accepted records of sightings in no more than two of the past 10 years.
extirpated: Species which was formerly "casual" or "regular" in Illinois but which has not been recorded from the wild in the state for at least 50 years.
extinct: Species which once occurred in Illinois but no longer occurs anywhere in the world.
* : Endangered/threatened status is show as of 1999.
Listing is updated regularly.
Visit http:// dnr.state.il.us/espb/index.htm for the latest information.
